name:                ministg
version:             0.1
cabal-version:       >= 1.2
synopsis:            ministg is an interpreter for a simple high-level operational semantics for the STG machine. 
description:         ministg is an interpreter for a simple high-level operational semantics for the STG machine. The
                     semantics is taken from the research paper "Making a fast curry: push/enter vs. eval/apply
                     for higher-order languages", by Simon Marlow and Simon Peyton Jones.
